Chelsea have released their squad that will take on Grimsby Town in tonight’s Carabao Cup third round fixture at Stamford Bridge. Chelsea manager, Frank Lampard, had already confirmed that defenders, Emerson Palmieri and Andreas Christensen will be out of action until next month. Chelsea head to the game following a 2-1 defeat to Liverpool in the Premier League over the weekend. Chelsea’s provisional squad against Grimsby: Caballero, Arrizabalaga, Azpilicueta, Zouma, Alonso, Jorginho, Mount, Giroud, Pedro, Pulisic, Kante, Tomori, Barkley, Kovacic, Willian, Abraham, Batshuayi, Reece James, Marc Guehi, Billy Gilmour, Hudson-Odoi. The kick-off time for the match is 7:45pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.